1. Ja *kapu* nosim kada je hladno. (I wear a *hat* when it's cold.)
2. Molim vas, *kapu* mi donesite, zaboravio sam je kod kuće. (Please bring me my *hat*, I forgot it at home.)
3. *Kapa* mi je pala na pod dok sam izlazio iz autobusa. (My *hat* fell on the floor as I was getting off the bus.)
4. Nisam mogao da nađem *kapu* u prodavnici, sve su bile rasprodane. (I couldn't find a *hat* in the store, they were all sold out.)
5. Ona je kupila predivnu *kapu* od vune. (She bought a beautiful woolen *hat*.)
6. Svi su bili oduševljeni njenom *kapom* sa pomponom. (Everyone was amazed by her *hat* with a pom-pom.)
7. Ovaj džemper se dobro slaže sa tvojom *kapom*. (This sweater goes well with your *hat*.)
8. On je zakačio *kapu* za granu drveta dok je bio u šumi. (He hooked his *hat* onto a tree branch while he was in the woods.) 
9. Zbog kiše, svi su nosili *kape* da zaštite svoje frizure. (Because of the rain, everyone wore *hats* to protect their hairstyles.)
10. Ovo je omiljena *kapa* mog dede, čuva je kao uspomenu na svoju mladost. (This is my grandpa's favorite *hat*, he keeps it as a memory of his youth.)